                     <interp inst="t18311201-215-defend1676" type="age" value="21"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18311201-215-off1149" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-215-off1149" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-215-off1149" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18311201-215-cd1150" type="crimeDate">1st of December</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-215-off1149 t18311201-215-cd1150"></join>, 1 box, value 6d.; 1 shawl, value 6d.; 2 frocks, value 6d.; 4 pinafores, value 4s.; 1 pair of shoes value 2s.; 2 handkerchiefs, value 1s.; 1 pair of stockings, value 6d.; 1 tippet, value 6d., and 1 1/2 yard of ribbon, value 6d.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t18311201-215-victim1678" type="victimName">
                     Edmond 
                     Bird
                  <interp inst="t18311201-215-victim1678" type="surname" value="Bird"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-215-victim1678" type="given" value="Edmond"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-215-victim1678" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-215-off1149 t18311201-215-victim1678"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>EDMOND BIRD. I <rs id="t18311201-215-viclabel1151" type="occupation">keep the George</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-215-victim1678 t18311201-215-viclabel1151"></join>, <placeName id="t18311201-215-crimeloc1152">West-street, Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-215-crimeloc1152" type="placeName" value="West-street, Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-215-crimeloc1152" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-215-off1149 t18311201-215-crimeloc1152"></join>. Last Thursday night, about six o'clock, a bandbox, containing these articles was put into a butcher's cart at my door, for my nephew to take with my daughter to South-street, Park-lane - the cart had not left the door ten minutes before I heard the box was stolen; my nephew is not here - he lives in the country; the prisoner was brought to my house in about half an hour, with the box, in the same state as before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-215-person1679">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BUSHNELL
               <interp inst="t18311201-215-person1679" type="surname" value="BUSHNELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-215-person1679" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-215-person1679" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a basket-maker, and live at the Crown, in West-street, Bird sent for me to mind the cart, which stood at his door; I saw his little girl and the box put in - there was a tail to the cart; it left the door a little after six o'clock - I went into the tap-room to finish a pint of beer, and heard the cart come back very quick Bird's nephew said the box was gone - Bird called me; I went out, and found the prisoner in Black Boy-alley, West-street, with another person, who had got the box; I passed them, and then returned back quick - they both made a full stop together; I said that was the box I was looking for, that it belonged to Mr. Bird - the prisoner then laid hold of it; I stopped and said, "I must have it" - the prisoner said, "No, let it be," and "I will put you in it;" it is a lonely place - I did not like to stop him; I took it from them, and told the prisoner I would not say who had possession of it; he gave it to me with great reluctance - the other never spoke; Bird insisted on knowing who I got it from, and I told him - I knew him before for some years; he jobbed for people.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-215-person1680">
                  THOMAS 
                  STALIAN
               <interp inst="t18311201-215-person1680" type="surname" value="STALIAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-215-person1680" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-215-person1680" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol of St. Sepulchre's. I apprehended the prisoner about half-past seven o'clock on Thursday evening, in King-street, Snow-hill; he had another person with him - I said I had information about him; he said I was deceived in my information - I said if so it would be better for him; I had received information of the cart being robbed, but all I told him was, that I had received information about him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was coming from my uncle's about half-past six o'clock, and met this young man in the alley, with the box; I knew him, and asked how he did - the witness came up, and took the box out of his hand.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18311201-215-verdict1153" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-215-verdict1153" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 21 - <rs id="t18311201-215-punish1154" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-215-punish1154" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-215-defend1676 t18311201-215-punish1154"></join>
               Transported for Seven Years
            </rs>.</p>
